The paper deals with the properties of context-free languages and finite automata on trees, which are typically studied in the formal language theory (cs.FL) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses decidability, which is a topic in logic and computation (cs.LO). The use of visibly pushdown languages and finite automata on trees suggests that the paper may also be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
